docs.abstract: “It could very well be that the crown prince had knowledge of this tragic event — maybe he did and maybe he didn’t!” President Trump said.
docs.snippet: “It could very well be that the crown prince had knowledge of this tragic event — maybe he did and maybe he didn’t!” President Trump said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump defied the nation’s intelligence agencies and a growing body of evidence on Tuesday to declare his unswerving loyalty to Saudi Arabia, asserting that Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman’s culpability for the killing of Jamal Khashoggi might never be known.

headline.main: In Extraordinary Statement, Trump Stands With Saudis Despite Khashoggi Killing
headline.print_headline: Trump Stands With Saudis Over Murder of Khashoggi

docs.abstract: Senate Democrats may block legislation proposed by their Republican counterparts that would allocate billions of dollars across the country, citing a push for more aid for Puerto Rico’s recovery.
docs.snippet: Senate Democrats may block legislation proposed by their Republican counterparts that would allocate billions of dollars across the country, citing a push for more aid for Puerto Rico’s recovery.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats next week may block legislation proposed by their Republican counterparts that would allocate billions of dollars for disaster recovery across the country, citing opposition from House Democrats and a push to add more aid to Puerto Rico’s slow efforts to recover from a pair of devastating hurricanes more than a year ago.

headline.main: Disaster Relief Bill at an Impasse Over Puerto Rico Aid
headline.print_headline: Impasse in Congress Over Disaster Aid Hangs on How Much Puerto Rico Is Due

docs.abstract: While a reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act passed the House Judiciary Committee, partisan debate over social issues could slow its final passage.
docs.snippet: While a reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act passed the House Judiciary Committee, partisan debate over social issues could slow its final passage.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Judiciary Committee voted along party lines on Wednesday to approve a reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act after Democrats turned back Republican attempts to gut protections of transgender people and restrict some gun ownership.

headline.main: Transgender and Gun Rights Are Sticking Points for Violence Against Women Act
headline.print_headline: Anti-Violence Measure Stirs Friction On Panel

docs.abstract: Negotiations over eliminating North Korea’s nuclear arsenal have made little progress since the two leaders’ June meeting in Singapore.
docs.snippet: Negotiations over eliminating North Korea’s nuclear arsenal have made little progress since the two leaders’ June meeting in Singapore.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump will meet with North Korea’s leader, Kim Jong-un, in late February, the White House announced on Friday, renewing a high-level diplomatic dialogue that has eased tensions with a rogue nuclear state but has shown no progress in eliminating its nuclear arsenal.

headline.main: Trump and Kim Jong-un to Hold Second Summit Meeting Next Month
headline.print_headline: President Plans Talks With Kim For Next Month
